title: Network
overview: A television network cynically exploits a deranged former anchor's ravings and revelations about the news media for its own profit.

title: Jungfrukällan
overview: An innocent yet pampered young virgin and her family's pregnant and jealous servant set out to deliver candles to church, but only one returns from events that transpire in the woods along the way.

title: Magnolia
overview: An epic mosaic of interrelated characters in search of love, forgiveness, and meaning in the San Fernando Valley.

title: Scent of a Woman
overview: A prep school student needing money agrees to "babysit" a blind man, but the job is not at all what he anticipated.

title: Hamlet
overview: Hamlet, Prince of Denmark, returns home to find his father murdered and his mother remarrying the murderer, his uncle. Meanwhile, war is brewing.

title: Udaan
overview: Expelled from his school, a 16-year old boy returns home to his abusive and oppressive father.

title: Nelyubov
overview: A couple going through a divorce must team up to find their son who has disappeared during one of their bitter arguments.

title: Philadelphia
overview: When a man with HIV is fired by his law firm because of his condition, he hires a homophobic small time lawyer as the only willing advocate for a wrongful dismissal suit.

title: Sling Blade
overview: Karl Childers, a simple man hospitalized since his childhood murder of his mother and her lover, is released to start a new life in a small town.

title: Beasts of No Nation
overview: A drama based on the experiences of Agu, a child soldier fighting in the civil war of an unnamed African country.

title: Bride of Frankenstein
overview: Mary Shelley reveals the main characters of her novel survived: Dr. Frankenstein, goaded by an even madder scientist, builds his monster a mate.

title: Rebel Without a Cause
overview: A rebellious young man with a troubled past comes to a new town, finding friends and enemies.

title: The Grapes of Wrath
overview: A poor Midwest family is forced off their land. They travel to California, suffering the misfortunes of the homeless in the Great Depression.

title: Paths of Glory
overview: After refusing to attack an enemy position, a general accuses the soldiers of cowardice and their commanding officer must defend them.

title: Freaks
overview: A circus' beautiful trapeze artist agrees to marry the leader of side-show performers, but his deformed friends discover she is only marrying him for his inheritance.

title: Auf der anderen Seite
overview: A Turkish man travels to Istanbul to find the daughter of his father's former girlfriend.

title: Room
overview: Held captive for 7 years in an enclosed space, a woman and her young son finally gain their freedom, allowing the boy to experience the outside world for the first time.

title: Roma
overview: A year in the life of a middle-class family's maid in Mexico City in the early 1970s.
stars: ['Yalitza Aparicio', 'Marina de Tavira', 'Diego Cortina Autrey', 'Carlos Peralta']

title: Jodaeiye Nader az Simin
overview: A married couple are faced with a difficult decision - to improve the life of their child by moving to another country or to stay in Iran and look after a deteriorating parent who has Alzheimer's disease.

title: Vozvrashchenie
overview: In the Russian wilderness, two brothers face a range of new, conflicting emotions when their father - a man they know only through a single photograph - resurfaces.
